review_blob:
Appearance: Thick white foam with small bubbles. Nose: Some tropical notes and some cat-pee. Taste: Lots of grape and more cat-stuff, good bitterness. Pretty good. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob:
This'll be my shortest review ever. This beer is a well executed Modus Hoperandi Clone. Just a teeny, weeny bit maltier and sweeter. Nice job. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is descent for a dark lager. Too bad it's called an IPA. Looks nice. Big off-white head and copper color. Aroma is earth and a hint of plastic. Very little hops. Taste is like described. I was taken aback by the really distinguished taste of lager and not ale. Quite malty for a lager though. If you reset your senses it's quite drinkable for that but there's a slightly sour taste in there that brings down the score. No hops in the aftertaste. It puzzles me why people insist on calling beer for something it isn't. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
UPDATED: FEB 16, 2015
beer_name: Amager / Surly Todd - The Axe Man

review_blob:
Is this a joke? Let's put hops on the bottle and call it green, IPA and fresh and maybe we can dupe some wanna-be hop heads that they're drinking the real thing. 

The beer had almost no head, has aroma of something lagerish and tastes NOTHING of hops. It reminds me like one of those beers you get a the worst pub in town where people drink beer because it's cheap and it's alcohol. Bad, bad, bad. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This was a pleasant surprise! A thin off-white head. Belgian aroma. A fruity, sweet, malty taste with maybe just a little too much alcohol. Is this a Belgian stout that I'm drinking? Very drinkable, well balanced. Recommended!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A big white not so dense head. Malt in the aroma and some hops. Initially the taste is a bit thin but after a while there are notes of peach, Basette winegums and hops. Very pleasant aftertaste and a nice bitterness to it. I like it!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: UPDATED: DEC 15, 2013

This was one of the worst beers out of the 100+ I tasted this year. Aroma: Non-distinct metallic, earthy and some slight smoke. No hops. Almost no head and very little carbonation. Taste was exactly like a moldy earth cellar. No hops and some sour maltiness. Quite horrible, I almost poured it into the sink. How this can be called an IPA is beyond me. Its more like a foul dark lager. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

After a large bottle this review is getting increasingly hard to write.
Nice foamy head that lingers which is the same as the aftertaste that has quite some bitterness to it. Aroma is pleasantly hoppy. Quite well balanced but not too complex taste as perhaps some other IPAs. Color is cloudy amber from the yeast in the bottle. Taste is a bit on the grassy side for an IPA. Very drinkable.

Nice foamy head, yeast and sour aroma. Initial taste reaction was, Oh this is sweet. After understanding that this more like a strong Belgian ale than anything like a barley wine it gets quite pleasant. In my personal opinion, perhaps a bit too sweet / too much alcohol. (13%) No hop-taste present. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle at Oliver Twist. 
Very low head, disappeared quite fast. Citrus yellow color. Strong bitterness , typically DIPA-like with an aftertaste that lingers for an hour. Almost menthol like. (Not bad for a hop head!) Taste is grassy, hoppy, some citrus and a little bit of well hidden alcohol. You really can't drink something else after this one. It's like Stones Ruination. This beer would really benefit from a better label design which looks like it's been made in Word in five minutes. Shame, 'cause it's a good beer!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Jag mste sga att jag r lite besviken. Jag hade bara druckit Neb frn OP innan och den r i vrldsklass. Hypnopompa har inget skum och ingen kolsyra. Det gr den lite oattraktiv och den doftar inte s mycket. Lite katrinplommon och rkt malt. Den r st, mycket st, ganska rkig/stoutig i smaken men dr en Stout ibland kan knnas som att tugga en bit svart tyskt brd brukar man f lite hjlp av kolsyran som lttar upp. Men inte hr allts. Sen r den stark, ver 10% vilket kanske gr att man inte bljar sig i den. Nej, bttre kan ni. Det hr var stolpe ut. Sorry. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is my second tasting of this beer. First time was in Las Vegas at the Freakin Frog. This time was in Sweden from Systembolaget (Oct 4. 2013). Aroma is citrus and hops. Quite light and fresh. Color is light amber and a 2-3 cm fading head. Taste is good. Lots of mango, citrus, tropical fruits. Very nice. Quite light on the malty side. Some sweetness and a rather strong bitter finish. Just a little to bitter to find the perfect balance in my opinion. This is a very good beer, but there are better. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Smells like teen... Sorry. It smells like honey and tastes very much of the same and a little bit of malt. Not much bitterness, rather quite sweet. Non-distinct hoppiness. Rather boring but drinkable if you're pregnant or the designated driver. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This one was off the shelf from Systembolaget in Sweden. Bought it yesterday the 14/8-13. Since I cheat with brewing myself I can tell that this beer isn't ready yet and needs to be stored at least 3-4 weeks more to round off the hop-taste. The taste from the dry hopping kills all other taste and aroma in this beer. It's way too grassy. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A: Beerbottle Brown with a two finger soft foam. Smells lovely of hops. First you taste the hops and then a sweet round malty taste and a warming but not overwhelming taste of alcohol. Long bitter and malty aftertaste. Great beer but personally I'd cut down on the alcohol one or two percent. (It's 9.6%)


---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle from ICA. Large frothy head and large bubbles. Dark amber color. Malty aroma and a nice flowery taste with a satisfying maltiness. Very nice bitterness at the end. Very, very good for a 3,5% lager.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wondefully refreshing. Very crisp and clean taste. Superb for a beer with low alcohol. Reminds me of good German pilsners because of the slight taste of iron in the water. Well done!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great aroma, very hoppy! Pours golden but not crystal clear. Initial taste is a nice bitterness but is followed by a quite unpleasant chemical aftertaste that reminds me of epoxy. Gets better with a few sips though. Bottle from ICA.


---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle bought from ICA Supermarket. 
Aroma: Yeast and Weibier. 
Taste: Corn, Weibier again and also some yeast. 
Aftertaste: Not so pleasant. Plastic and metallic but diminishing after a few gulps.

Underbar humlig doft slr mot en och en hg fast krona som aldrig vill frsvinna. Min l var inte klar som ngon skrev utan disig men vacker brnstensfrgad. Tyvrr grusas hela smakupplevelsen av en stickande epoxismak, det vill sga fenoler. Synd, fr den hr hade verkligen potential.

33l bottle from ICA maxi in Nacka.
Huge white, dense white head with very fine bubbles. My four year ols son noted from one meter away that it smells like corn and it sure does. Taste is also corn, wheat, bread and a little sweet. Color is foggy golden. Quite alright for a 3,5% vol beer but a little to sweet and too much corn taste for me.
